<paragraph blockId="3.[106,745,522,1130]" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">
R e m a r k s. The main differences of 
<taxonomicName authority="(PERNER, 1903)" baseAuthorityName="PERNER" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="incola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">Schizocrania incola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Perner, J." box="[201,368,554,577]" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" refId="ref9862" refString="Perner, J. (1903): Gasteropodes. - In: Barrande, J., Systeme silurien du Centre de la Boheme, Volume IV, tome 1. R. Gerhard, Fr. Rivnac, Leipsic, Prague, 164 pp., 89 pls." type="book" year="1903">PERNER, 1903</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the ancestral 
<taxonomicName authority="(HAVLICEK, 1972)" baseAuthorityName="HAVLICEK" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Ptychopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="hornyi">
<emphasis box="[634,647,554,577]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[672,745,554,577]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">hornyi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Havlicek, V." box="[114,286,587,610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" pagination="229 - 234" refId="ref8693" refString="Havlicek, V. (1972): Life habit of some Ordovician inarticulate brachiopods. - Vestnik Ustredniho ustavu geologickeho, 47: 229 - 234." type="journal article" year="1972">HAVLÍČEK, 1972</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
are the high convexity of the dorsal valve, highly arcuate anterior commissure, and finer (capillate instead of costellate) ornamentation in the dorsal valve. The last difference is the most significant. The number of costellae near the anterior margin ranges between 2–4 costellae per 
<quantity box="[255,320,749,772]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
in the largest preserved dorsal valves 
<taxonomicName authority="(REED, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="REED" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[106,397,782,805]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="multistriata">
<emphasis box="[106,253,782,805]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S. multistriata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reed, F. R. C." box="[266,390,782,805]" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" pagination="444 - 454" refId="ref9960" refString="Reed, F. R. C. (1905): New fossils from the Haverfordwest district, IV. - Geological Magazine, Decade 5, 2: 444 - 454. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0016756800128377" type="journal article" year="1905">REED, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="HAVLICEK" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[446,539,782,805]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Ptychopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="hornyi">
<emphasis box="[446,539,782,805]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S. hornyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but there is at least 7–8 costellae in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PERNER" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[291,389,814,837]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="incola">
<emphasis box="[291,389,814,837]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S. incola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 3, Figs 9, 11, 12–14). This difference is even more striking because the number of costellae per 
<quantity box="[248,310,879,902]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
in all species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="HALL et WHITFIELD" authorityYear="1875" box="[496,635,879,902]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[496,635,879,902]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">Schizocrania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
decreases with the shell size, and the measured valves of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PERNER" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[611,705,912,935]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="incola">
<emphasis box="[611,705,912,935]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S. incola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger than the largest available valves of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="REED" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[549,699,944,967]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="multistriata">
<emphasis box="[549,699,944,967]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S. multistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="HAVLICEK" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[106,208,977,1000]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Ptychopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="hornyi">
<emphasis box="[106,208,977,1000]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S. hornyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PERNER" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[226,447,977,1000]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="incola">
<emphasis box="[226,447,977,1000]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">Schizocrania incola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also prominent in high convexity of the dorsal valve. One of the 
<typeStatus box="[551,597,1009,1032]" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PERNER" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[106,197,1042,1065]" class="Lingulata" family="Trematidae" genus="Schizocrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lingulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="228" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="incola">
<emphasis box="[106,197,1042,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">S. incola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NM-L 5404) shows a distinct impression of a large visceral area, with clearly defined anterior projection (
<figureCitation box="[113,227,1107,1130]" captionStart="Text-fig" captionStartId="1.[106,189,634,655]" captionTargetBox="[111,739,150,596]" captionTargetId="figure-846@1.[99,740,138,596]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Text-fig. 1. Schizocrania incola (PERNER, 1903). Drawings of visceral area and muscle scars." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5387930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5387930/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">Text-fig. 1</figureCitation>
, Pl. 3, Fig. 16).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[106,745,1154,1210]" pageId="3" pageNumber="228">O c c u r r e n c e. Letná Formation, upper part (mid- to late Sandbian) (localities: Trubská gorge, Zahořany).</paragraph>
